<br>
In exp groups, they are great when I can get it, suck sitting LFG seeing other classes put right in groups.  When I do get groups I make it a mission to show my classes abilities, I take screenshots of tanks saying "why is my health not going down" when im the only healer, or 'nice pulling Fris', or 'thanks for the buffs Fris', and my fav after getting settled in group, 'wow we rocking now'.  <br>
<br>
On raids its different.  I'd probably trade my class for a number of others, not clerics though.   I'd like to know I really bring something to the raid, damage as a monk/warrior/rogue or wizard.  Druids just don't help raids enough in my opinion.   <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65433>fris</a>

